      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Nonconjugated <i>β</i>,<i>γ</i>-unsaturated ketones, such as 3-cyclohexenone, are in an acid-catalyzed equilibrium with their conjugated <i>α</i>,<i>β</i>-unsaturated isomers. Propose a mechanism for the isomerization.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaEVZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--79efcf98f6d59a6bda93206f4ee5b1b03c46467c/OChem_22_EC_019.jpg\" alt=\"3-cyclohexenone with alpha, beta, and gamma carbons indicated and a double-bond between the beta and gamma carbons reacts with acid to form 2-cyclohexenone with a double-bond between the alpha and beta carbons.\">",
